text: Semenov Peak () is a mountain in the Tian Shan on the border between Kyrgyzstan and Kazakhstan. The 5816m high mountain is located 8.64 km northwest of Khan Tengri (6995 m) on the opposite side of the Northern Engilchek Glacier. == History == The peak is named for the Russian geographer Peter Semenov-Tian-Shansky. ==References== Category:Mountains of Kazakhstan Category:Mountains of Kyrgyzstan Category:Five-thousanders of the Tian Shan Category:Issyk-Kul Region Category:Landforms of Almaty Region Category:Kazakhstan–Kyrgyzstan border Category:International mountains of Asia
title: Semenov Peak
